WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.279
this evening, the book of Acts.

00:00:03.279 --> 00:00:04.280
The book of Acts.

00:00:04.280 --> 00:00:07.320
And we'll begin in the 13th chapter this evening.

00:00:07.320 --> 00:00:10.720
And I'll read just a couple of verses of scripture, we'll look at a number of other portions of

00:00:10.720 --> 00:00:12.359
scripture as well.

00:00:12.359 --> 00:00:14.479
But you'll be familiar with this text.

00:00:14.479 --> 00:00:17.680
This is the record of the first missionary journey.

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:21.120
And I want to read just a couple of verses of scripture and then I'll give you the title

00:00:21.120 --> 00:00:24.360
for tonight and look at some things here.

00:00:24.360 --> 00:00:27.659
Acts chapter 13, beginning in verse number 1.

00:00:27.659 --> 00:00:32.459
The Bible says this, now there were in the church that was at Antioch certain prophets

00:00:32.459 --> 00:00:38.220
and teachers, as Barnabas and Simeon, that was called Niger, and Lucius of Cyrene and

00:00:38.220 --> 00:00:43.500
Menaean, which had been brought up with Herod the Tetrarch and Saul.

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:47.619
Notice this in verse 2, it says, as they ministered to the Lord.

00:00:47.619 --> 00:00:51.060
And it's good to be involved in ministry, it's good to be serving the Lord.

00:00:51.060 --> 00:00:54.819
It's good to be using your spiritual gift for God's glory.

00:00:54.819 --> 00:00:59.099
And every single one of us have a spiritual gift, and as we use our spiritual gifts for

00:00:59.099 --> 00:01:02.419
God's honor and His glory, He blesses and uses us.

00:01:02.419 --> 00:01:04.980
It says, as they ministered to the Lord.

00:01:04.980 --> 00:01:08.019
And then notice this, it says, and fasted.

00:01:08.019 --> 00:01:14.260
And we understand the importance of fasting, oftentimes it's something that's really missing

00:01:14.260 --> 00:01:15.940
in our churches today.

00:01:15.940 --> 00:01:22.980
In fact, I shared with someone not long ago that dietary intermittent fasting became popular.

00:01:22.980 --> 00:01:27.660
I don't know how popular it is still now, but for a period of time there were more people

00:01:27.660 --> 00:01:32.099
talking about intermittent fasting than they ever talked about spiritual fasting and the

00:01:32.099 --> 00:01:35.620
aspect of biblical truth with regard to fasting.

00:01:35.620 --> 00:01:37.620
But we see the Bible says, and they fasted.

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:42.459
And then notice the Holy Ghost said, I'm thankful for God's leadership, the Holy Spirit of God,

00:01:42.459 --> 00:01:45.059
He gives leadership and direction.

00:01:45.059 --> 00:01:51.500
Notice what the Lord says, the Holy Ghost says, separate me, Barnabas and Saul, for

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:57.059
the work whereunto I have called them.

00:01:57.059 --> 00:02:03.779
And when they had fasted and prayed and laid their hands on them, they sent them away.

00:02:03.779 --> 00:02:08.500
From verse number three, I want to just take that phrase and use it as our title this evening,

00:02:08.500 --> 00:02:11.500
when they had fasted and prayed.

00:02:11.500 --> 00:02:15.259
At this time, and I know his name is Saul, it will be changed here very shortly, but

00:02:15.259 --> 00:02:17.139
I'll refer to him as Paul.

00:02:17.139 --> 00:02:20.860
Paul was the one being sent out from the church in Antioch.

00:02:20.860 --> 00:02:22.339
It was the first missionary journey.

00:02:22.339 --> 00:02:26.619
And I believe that this church in Antioch, as we begin to understand some things about

00:02:26.619 --> 00:02:32.660
the church, we see that they had an understanding of the privilege and power of prayer.

00:02:32.660 --> 00:02:33.660
They're a praying church.

00:02:33.660 --> 00:02:39.899
In fact, as we look at the text of Scripture, I believe that this church had placed an obvious

00:02:39.899 --> 00:02:42.940
emphasis upon prayer.

00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:47.940
And you know, it's an important thing when we understand the privilege of prayer, but

00:02:47.940 --> 00:02:52.139
we also take and make a priority to pray.

00:02:52.139 --> 00:02:54.300
And prayer is so vital.

00:02:54.300 --> 00:03:00.419
And we find that as we look through Acts 13 and 14 that provide us with the account of

00:03:00.419 --> 00:03:05.220
what happened on this first missionary journey, I believe that we could say this, God did

00:03:05.220 --> 00:03:07.279
some amazing things.

00:03:07.279 --> 00:03:09.500
God worked in miraculous ways.

00:03:09.500 --> 00:03:14.539
God blessed and God used these men as they were separated for the work that God called

00:03:14.539 --> 00:03:15.539
them to.

00:03:15.639 --> 00:03:20.539
I believe that as you look at the text and you begin to see what's happened, there's

00:03:20.539 --> 00:03:26.460
no doubt in my mind that God worked because His people prayed.

00:03:26.460 --> 00:03:28.039
Because His people prayed.

00:03:28.039 --> 00:03:33.020
God has ordained it that prayer moves the hand of God.

00:03:33.020 --> 00:03:38.539
And that's just a biblical truth, a biblical reality.

00:03:38.539 --> 00:03:43.979
As we study through the New Testament, we find that the Apostle Paul is enlisting fellow

00:03:44.419 --> 00:03:48.899
believers, it seems at every turn, to pray for him.

00:03:48.899 --> 00:03:53.979
We find that he obviously, the Apostle Paul, we can read of the prayers that he prayed

00:03:53.979 --> 00:04:00.179
for those in Ephesus, those in Colossae, and others that he encourages them by telling

00:04:00.179 --> 00:04:01.979
them that he's praying for them.

00:04:01.979 --> 00:04:03.580
And he was a man of prayer.

00:04:03.580 --> 00:04:07.779
He understood the importance of prayer, but he also understood the power of prayer in

00:04:07.779 --> 00:04:10.740
having others pray for him.

00:04:10.740 --> 00:04:15.020
And he asks many times for others to pray for him.

00:04:15.020 --> 00:04:19.299
You may know the phrase, maybe it's something that you've heard at some point before, the

00:04:19.299 --> 00:04:21.619
phrase, hold the ropes.

00:04:21.619 --> 00:04:26.420
And that phrase became popular when William Carey, the missionary to India, made this

00:04:26.420 --> 00:04:27.820
full statement.

00:04:27.820 --> 00:04:33.339
He said, I will go down into the pit if you will hold the ropes.

00:04:33.339 --> 00:04:38.880
And what he was communicating through that statement was that really an oft-repeated

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:45.239
part of that, hold the ropes, what he's communicating is that for him, he was going to go.

00:04:45.239 --> 00:04:47.500
And for others, they were going to stay.

00:04:47.500 --> 00:04:53.720
But those that were staying had a vital part in the ministry of what he would accomplish

00:04:53.720 --> 00:05:00.760
or what God would do through him as they would engage in intercessory prayer, that they would

00:05:00.760 --> 00:05:06.160
understand that it was not just that William Carey is going to India and he and his family

00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:13.000
are going there and think that they have no part of the ministry, no, I will go as

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:18.959
you hold the ropes, as you pray on this end.

00:05:18.959 --> 00:05:23.019
What a blessing to know that people are praying for you.

00:05:23.019 --> 00:05:29.959
This evening, just as Paul enlisted prayer warriors, I want to not only personally but

00:05:29.959 --> 00:05:35.600
as a representative of the group that's going to Idaho on Monday, I want to request your

00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:37.600
prayers for us.

00:05:37.600 --> 00:05:43.160
And I'm looking forward to the trip, I'm looking forward to what God will do, but I'm absolutely

00:05:43.160 --> 00:05:51.279
convinced in my heart this evening that God will only work as the people of God are praying.

00:05:51.279 --> 00:05:58.079
And as God moves in your heart and as you pray for those that are going, then God will

00:05:58.079 --> 00:05:59.079
do a great work.

00:05:59.079 --> 00:06:03.640
And here's the thing, for many of you, you will not get on a plane Monday morning and

00:06:03.640 --> 00:06:11.000
go to Idaho with us, but you will have a vital part in that trip as you have an opportunity

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:14.859
to stay here and to pray for us.

00:06:14.859 --> 00:06:18.399
And as we look at this truth throughout the New Testament, again, I started here in Acts

00:06:18.399 --> 00:06:25.799
13, because here in Acts 13, the apostle Paul understood that the church in Antioch, it

00:06:25.799 --> 00:06:31.480
says that when they had fasted and prayed and laid their hands on them, they sent them

00:06:31.480 --> 00:06:32.480
away.

00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:37.959
And so Paul understood that they were praying for him, and he sees what God does.

00:06:37.959 --> 00:06:44.140
He experiences firsthand throughout chapters 13 and 14, he experiences what God is able

00:06:44.140 --> 00:06:50.279
to accomplish and how God is able to work, and so therefore throughout the number of

00:06:50.279 --> 00:06:55.160
writings that we read of Paul, often he's asking, would you pray?

00:06:55.160 --> 00:06:56.440
Would you pray?

00:06:56.440 --> 00:06:57.440
Would you pray?

00:06:57.440 --> 00:06:59.880
And so this evening I want to start and I want to look at a number of these.

00:06:59.880 --> 00:07:05.959
Look in Romans chapter 15, if you will, in Romans chapter 15, and I want to note as we

00:07:05.959 --> 00:07:13.200
look at each of these portions of Scripture, I want to note the request, but also some

00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:18.059
details about the request, because each one is not identical.

00:07:18.059 --> 00:07:24.720
We find in Romans 15 that the apostle Paul had a desire, obviously, to preach the gospel.

00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:27.959
We start in the first chapter of the book of Romans where he says he's not ashamed of

00:07:27.959 --> 00:07:32.839
the gospel of Christ, and he wants to go forth and to preach the gospel.

00:07:32.839 --> 00:07:37.299
We find in verse number 30, notice what Paul says, now I beseech you.

00:07:37.299 --> 00:07:39.100
We understand that to be strong language.

00:07:39.100 --> 00:07:41.959
We use, we see that word used throughout the New Testament.

00:07:41.959 --> 00:07:45.399
The word beseech really carries with it the idea of begging.

00:07:45.399 --> 00:07:46.600
I beseech you.

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:50.959
What is it that Paul, at this point as he's nearing the end of the epistle, what is he

00:07:50.959 --> 00:07:54.839
begging, beseeching the brethren to do?

00:07:54.839 --> 00:07:59.399
He says, I beseech you, brethren, for the Lord Jesus Christ's sake and for the love

00:07:59.399 --> 00:08:00.559
of the Spirit.

00:08:00.559 --> 00:08:10.519
Notice this, that you strive together with me in your prayers to God for me.

00:08:10.519 --> 00:08:17.359
So Paul is beseeching these brethren, and he's saying to them that you strive together

00:08:17.359 --> 00:08:21.720
with me in your prayers to God for me.

00:08:21.720 --> 00:08:27.679
We see this striving together idea that is given to us here in verse number 30, and how

00:08:27.679 --> 00:08:33.159
that these would have an opportunity to pray for the apostle Paul as he would go forth

00:08:33.159 --> 00:08:36.239
to preach the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:08:36.239 --> 00:08:42.400
But he continues in verse number 31, notice that I may be delivered from them that do

00:08:42.400 --> 00:08:44.840
not believe in Judea.

00:08:44.840 --> 00:08:49.840
You understand that when we go forth, when you go to carry the gospel, when we go out

00:08:49.840 --> 00:08:56.200
on Saturday mornings to knock on people's doors to tell them about Jesus, not everyone

00:08:56.200 --> 00:08:58.719
is excited to see us.

00:08:58.719 --> 00:09:00.239
Amen?

00:09:00.239 --> 00:09:06.280
There are some that as we will go to Idaho that will not be excited that we're there

00:09:06.280 --> 00:09:12.520
trying to preach the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ to them, and Paul encountered that

00:09:12.520 --> 00:09:16.080
