00:09:16.080 --> 00:09:19.159
Some believed, and some did not.

00:09:19.479 --> 00:09:24.679
And Paul had that experience, and Paul understood what it was to deal, we read even in that

00:09:24.679 --> 00:09:29.719
first missionary journey of the persecution that he faced, and the opposition that he

00:09:29.719 --> 00:09:30.719
dealt with.

00:09:30.719 --> 00:09:36.119
And so he says, as he asked them to pray that I may be delivered from them that do not believe

00:09:36.119 --> 00:09:42.640
in Judea, and that my service, which I have for Jerusalem, may be accepted of the saints.

00:09:42.640 --> 00:09:46.799
And we believe that that has to do with really what we're dealing with on Sunday mornings,

00:09:46.799 --> 00:09:51.359
with that offering that he was taking back, and he's praying that he would be able to

00:09:51.359 --> 00:09:58.000
get that and accomplish really the idea when he says that my service which I have for Jerusalem

00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:00.039
may be accepted of the saints.

00:10:00.039 --> 00:10:01.639
not only that it would be a blessing to them,

00:10:01.639 --> 00:10:04.939
but the idea of fulfilling a ministry obligation

00:10:04.939 --> 00:10:07.559
and understanding that he had been entrusted with this.

00:10:07.559 --> 00:10:08.839
And we started looking at it

00:10:08.839 --> 00:10:11.399
in 2 Corinthians 8 a few weeks ago.

00:10:11.399 --> 00:10:13.919
We'll continue this Sunday morning.

00:10:13.919 --> 00:10:16.599
And we see that this is what Paul is referencing here,

00:10:16.599 --> 00:10:18.239
that I may come, verse 32,

00:10:18.239 --> 00:10:21.039
unto you with joy by the will of God,

00:10:21.039 --> 00:10:22.919
and may with you be refreshed.

00:10:22.919 --> 00:10:25.599
Now the God of peace be with you all, amen.

00:10:25.599 --> 00:10:27.559
And so we find that as Paul is writing,

00:10:27.559 --> 00:10:29.679
and of course, nearing the end of the epistle,

00:10:30.119 --> 00:10:35.119
